What is an Operator?
An operator is a symbol that performs an operation on one or more operands (values or variables).

Example: 
int c = a + b;
+ ‚Üí operator
a, b ‚Üí operands
= ‚Üí assignment operator

Types of Operators 
Java has 8 main types of operators:

1Ô∏è Arithmetic Operators
2Ô∏è Assignment Operators
3Ô∏è Relational (Comparison) Operators
4Ô∏è Logical Operators
5Ô∏è Unary Operators
6Ô∏è Increment & Decrement Operators
7Ô∏è Conditional (Ternary) Operator
8Ô∏è Bitwise Operators 

1Ô∏è Arithmetic Operators
üëâ Used to perform mathematical operations
Operator		Meaning						Example
	+				Addition						a + b
	-				Subtraction					a - b
	*				Multiplication				a * b
	/				Division						a / b
	%				Modulus (remainder)	a % b

2Ô∏è Assignment Operators
üëâ Used to assign values to variables
Operator		Meaning						Example
	=				Assign							a = 10
	+=			Add & assign				a += 5
	-=				Subtract & assign		a -= 3
	*=			Multiply & assign		a *= 2
	/=				Divide & assign			a /= 2
	%=			Mod & assign				a %= 2

3Ô∏è Relational (Comparison) Operators
üëâ Used to compare two values
üëâ Result is boolean (true or false)
Operator		Meaning
	==			Equal to
	!=				Not equal
	>				Greater than
	<				Less than
	>=			Greater than or equal
	<=			Less than or equal

4Ô∏è  Logical Operators
üëâ Used with boolean conditions
Operator			Meaning
	&&	 			Logical AND
	!					Logical NOT
	|| 					Logical OR

5Ô∏è Unary Operators
üëâ Operate on single operand
Operator		Meaning			Example
	+				Unary plus			+a
	-				Unary minus		-a
	!				Logical NOT		!true

6Ô∏è Increment & Decrement Operators
üëâ Increase or decrease value by 1
Operator			Meaning
	++				Increment
	--					Decrement
Pre vs Post (VERY IMPORTANT)

7Ô∏è Conditional (Ternary) Operator
üëâ Short form of if‚Äìelse
Syntax
condition ? value_if_true : value_if_false;
Ex: int max = (a > b) ? a : b;

8Ô∏è  Bitwise Operators (Intro)
üëâ Operate on binary values
Operator		Meaning
	&				AND
	^				XOR
	~				NOT
	<<			Left shift
	>>			Right shift


****** Summary Table ******
 
Category					Purpose
Arithmetic				Mathematical operations
Assignment				Assign values
Relational				Compare values
Logical					Combine conditions
Unary						Single operand
Inc/Dec					Increase / decrease
Ternary					Short if‚Äìelse
